{"parse":{"title":"Lirnyk","pageid":2094451,"revid":841521662,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Lirnik_wioskowy.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Lirnik_wioskowy.jpg/220px-Lirnik_wioskowy.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"313\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Lirnik_wioskowy.jpg/330px-Lirnik_wioskowy.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Lirnik_wioskowy.jpg/440px-Lirnik_wioskowy.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4841\" data-file-height=\"6897\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Lirnik_wioskowy.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://polona.pl/item/lirnik-wioskowy-do-utworu-syrokomli,NzQ3ODE4ODI/\">Lirnyk</a></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:1902_Conference.jpeg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a7/1902_Conference.jpeg/200px-1902_Conference.jpeg\" width=\"200\" height=\"120\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a7/1902_Conference.jpeg/300px-1902_Conference.jpeg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a7/1902_Conference.jpeg/400px-1902_Conference.jpeg 2x\" data-file-width=\"450\" data-file-height=\"270\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:1902_Conference.jpeg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ukrainian lirnyk with kobzari, Kharkiv, 1902.</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Kharkiv_kobzari.jpeg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Kharkiv_kobzari.jpeg/200px-Kharkiv_kobzari.jpeg\" width=\"200\" height=\"125\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Kharkiv_kobzari.jpeg/300px-Kharkiv_kobzari.jpeg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Kharkiv_kobzari.jpeg/400px-Kharkiv_kobzari.jpeg 2x\" data-file-width=\"600\" data-file-height=\"376\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Kharkiv_kobzari.jpeg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ukrainian lirnyk with kobzari, Okhtyrka, 1911.</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>lirnyk</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Ukrainian_language\" title=\"Ukrainian language\">Ukrainian</a>: \u043b\u0456\u0440\u043d\u0438\u043a; plural \u043b\u0456\u0440\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0438 - lirnyky) were itinerant <a href=\"/wiki/Ukrainians\" title=\"Ukrainians\">Ukrainian</a> musicians who performed religious, historical and epic songs to the accompaniment of a <a href=\"/wiki/Lira_(instrument)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lira (instrument)\">lira</a>, the Ukrainian version of the hurdy-gurdy.\n</p><p>Lirnyky were similar to and belonged to the same guilds as the better known <a href=\"/wiki/Bandura\" title=\"Bandura\">bandura</a> players known as <a href=\"/wiki/Kobzar\" title=\"Kobzar\">kobzars</a>. However, the lirnyk played the lira, a kind of crank-driven <a href=\"/wiki/Hurdy-gurdy\" title=\"Hurdy-gurdy\">hurdy-gurdy</a>, while the kobzars played the lute-like <a href=\"/wiki/Bandura\" title=\"Bandura\">banduras</a>. Lirnyky were usually blind or had some major disability. They were active in all areas of Ukraine from (at least) the 17th century on. \n</p><p>The tradition was discontinued in Eastern/Central Ukraine in the mid-1930s, some lirnyky were seen in the regions of Western Ukraine until the 1970s and even the 1980s. \n</p><p>Today, the repertoire of the instrument is mostly performed by educated, sighted performers. Notable performers of the lira include <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mykhailo_Khai&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Mykhailo Khai (page does not exist)\">Mykhailo Khai</a>, Vadim (<a href=\"/wiki/Yarema\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Yarema\">Yarema</a>) Shevchuk, and <a href=\"/wiki/Volodymyr_Kushpet\" title=\"Volodymyr Kushpet\">Volodymyr Kushpet</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lirnyk&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Blind_musicians\" title=\"Blind musicians\">Blind musicians</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Bandurist\" title=\"Bandurist\">Bandurist</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Hurdy-gurdy\" title=\"Hurdy-gurdy\">Hurdy-gurdy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Kobzar\" title=\"Kobzar\">Kobzar</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Persecuted_bandurists\" title=\"Persecuted bandurists\">Persecuted bandurists</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sources\">Sources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lirnyk&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Sources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Humeniuk, A. - <i>Ukrainski narodni muzychni instrumenty</i> - Kiev: <a href=\"/wiki/Naukova_dumka\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Naukova dumka\">Naukova dumka</a>, 1967</li>\n<li>Mizynec, V. - <i>Ukrainian Folk Instruments</i> - Melbourne: Bayda books, 1984</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1331\nCached time: 20180905040427\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.016 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.025 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 23/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHi